Program: Outlook
Title: 03/02/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00d875c
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 4 Feb 2011
ZAINAB SALBI As the daughter of Saddam Hussein's personal pilot, Zainab Salbi grew up in his shadow. She tells us how she married her way out of Iraq, and went on to found "Women for Women International" which supports women in current and former conflict zones. ADAM AND NEIL PEARSON A condition called neurofibromatosis type one, or NF1, has left twins Adam and Neil Pearson looking very different from each other. Adam describes what he went through as a child as his head became misshapen and enlarged. Neil tells us he's also been affected, but less obviously - with epilepsy and memory loss. Show less